article.headline: Binghamton 80, Mansfield 62
article.story: EDS: APNewsNow. Binghamton 80, Mansfield 62. VESTAL, N.Y. -- D.J. Rivera, playing in his first game since transferring from Saint Joseph's, had 28 points and 10 rebounds to lead Binghamton to an 80-62 victory over Mansfield on Monday night. The Bearcats (1-0) shot 52 percent from the field but went just 16-of-37 from the free throw line to keep the Division II Mounties within striking distance. Rivera was 11-of-20 from the field and had four alley-oop dunks in the second half, when he scored 20 points. Binghamton missed five of its first six shots and led 16-14 with 10:36 to play in the half. But the Bearcats went on a 12-2 run and led 35-24 at halftime. Emanuel Mayben had 16 points and seven assists for Binghamton. Ryan Callahan had 17 points for the Mountaineers (1-1).
